 # State Spec v0.1[m
 [m
 ## Event Types[m
[31m-- `ALLOCATE` — mint/enable slots `0..8` for `userPubKey`[m
[31m-- `COMMIT` — bind `tokenID` to `recipientHash` with `tag`, optional `reasonHash`[m
[31m-- `UNBOND` — start quiet-unbond timer for `tokenID`[m
[31m-- `REVOKE` — finalize removal of an active commitment (post-delay)[m
[31m-- `RECOVER` — rotate keys/guardians; includes previous key, new key, and proof[m
[31m-- *(Optional)* `VERIFY` — device/passkey attestation record[m
[31m-- *(Optional)* `REKEY` — cohort pepper rotation announcement[m
[32m+[m[32m- `ALLOCATE` ï¿½ enable 9 DBT slots for `userPubKey`[m
[32m+[m[32m- `COMMIT` ï¿½ bind `slotID` ? `recipientHash` with `tag`, optional `reasonHash`[m
[32m+[m[32m- `UNBOND` ï¿½ start quiet-unbond timer (`unbondAt`)[m
[32m+[m[32m- `REVOKE` ï¿½ finalize removal post-delay; frees slot; sets `cooldownUntil`[m
[32m+[m[32m- `RECOVER` ï¿½ rotate keys/guardians: `{ oldPubKey, newPubKey, guardians[], proof }`[m
[32m+[m[32m- `VERIFY_DEVICE` ï¿½ device/passkey attestation record (Magic.link)[m
[32m+[m[32m- `CONTACT_ADD` ï¿½ `{ ownerId, contactId, channel, ts }`[m
[32m+[m[32m- `CONTACT_REMOVE` ï¿½ remove contact[m
[32m+[m[32m- `REKEY` ï¿½ cohort pepper rotation announcement[m
[32m+[m[32m- `CHECKPOINT` ï¿½ indexer announces `{ merkleRoot, schemaHash, height, ts }` to checkpoint topic[m
 [m
 ## Required Fields (all events)[m
[31m-`{ schema: "trustmesh/state/0.1", chainId, topicId, txId, ts, userPubKey, tokenID, nonce, sig }`[m
[31m-[m
[31m-Plus per-type fields:[m
[31m-- `COMMIT`: `{ recipientHash, tag, reasonHash?, cooldownUntil? }`[m
[31m-- `UNBOND`: `{ tokenID, unbondAt }`[m
[31m-- `REVOKE`: `{ tokenID, revokeAt }`[m
[31m-- `RECOVER`: `{ oldPubKey, newPubKey, guardians[], proof }`[m
[32m+[m[32m{ schema:"trustmesh/state/0.1", chainId, topicId, txId, ts,[m
[32m+[m[32m  userPubKey, slotID?, nonce, sig, cohortId, pepperVersion }[m
 [m
 ## Rules[m
[31m-- **Idempotency:** `(userPubKey, tokenID, nonce)` unique.[m
[31m-- **Validity:** tokenID ? [0..8]; only one active commitment per tokenID.[m
[31m-- **Cooldown:** per-slot; `COMMIT` invalid if now < `cooldownUntil`.[m
[31m-- **Ordering:** indexers must process by `(ts, txId)`; ties broken by `txId`.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Idempotency:** `(userPubKey, (slotID|eventKey), nonce)` unique[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Slots:** `slotID ? [0..8]`; **one active commitment per slot**[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Quiet Unbonding:** default **72h** between `UNBOND` and `REVOKE`[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Cooldown:** per-slot; default **14 days**; `COMMIT` invalid if `now < cooldownUntil`[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Contacts:** unlimited; private by default; low weight (policy below)[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Ordering:** reduce by `(ts, txId)`; tie-break on `txId`[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Checkpoint cadence:** **hourly** Merkle to dedicated HCS topic; verifiers must check continuity[m
 [m
[31m-## Checkpointing[m
[31m-- Indexers produce hourly Merkle roots over deterministic state.[m
[31m-- Publish `{ merkleRoot, schemaHash, height, ts }` to a dedicated HCS topic.[m
[32m+[m[32m## Pseudonymity[m
[32m+[m[32m`recipientHash` and user IDs = `HMAC_SHA256(cohortPepper[vX], E164(phone)|walletAlias)`; peppers via HKDF; stored in KMS/HSM.[m
