 # Glossary[m
 [m
[31m-- **Commit (verb):** Allocate one trust slot to a recipient.[m
[31m-- **Quiet Unbonding:** Delay period before a commitment is revoked.[m
[31m-- **Checkpoint:** Merkle-root summary of deterministic state.[m
[31m-- **Cohort Pepper:** Secret used for HMAC pseudonymization per cohort.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Device-Bound Token (DBT):** One of a userï¿½s **nine** commitment slots; bound to device key; non-transferable; revocable.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Circle of Trust:** The 9-slot strong trust model with quiet unbonding & cooldown.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Contact (Lite Trust):** Unlimited, consented connection used for discovery/routing; private by default; low analytic weight.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Quiet Unbonding:** ~72h delay before commitment removal; reduces social shock.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Checkpoint:** Hourly Merkle root of reduced state published to HCS.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Hashinal:** Portable Hedera-native reputation artifact (non-financial).[m
[32m+[m[32m- **TRST:** Scendï¿½s stablecoin rail on Hedera; **Brale handles KYC/AML**.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **KNS:** Human-readable Send-to-Name addressing with reservation/rename policy.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **XMTP:** End-to-end encrypted wallet chat; **not SMS**.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Cohort Pepper:** Secret used to derive pseudonymous IDs per cohort; versioned & rotated.[m
